==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fungia
<hw>Fun"gi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>fungus</ets> mushroom: cf. F. <ets>fongie</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of simple, stony corals; -- so called
because they are usually flat and circular, with radiating plates, like
the gills of a mushroom. Some of them are eighteen inches in
diameter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fungian</ent>⟦br⟧
